<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1403,1575]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">
Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Petrovitz, R." box="[312,537,1403,1430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" pagination="38 - 68" refId="ref30828" refString="Petrovitz, R. (1958) Das Subgenus Pygopleurus Motsch. der Gattung Amphicoma Latr. (Col. Scarabaeidae, Glaphyrinae). Entomologisk Tidskrift, 78 (Supplement), 38 - 68." type="journal article" year="1958">Petrovitz (1958: 50)</bibRefCitation>
clearly states “ 
<emphasis box="[708,1148,1404,1430]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Туре und Kotypen in meiner Sammlung</emphasis>
” [type and cotypes in my collection], his collection (in 
<collectionCode box="[478,565,1440,1466]" country="Switzerland" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/2jyg-xmd2" name="Museum d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" type="Museum">MHNG</collectionCode>
) includes only 
<specimenCount box="[735,886,1440,1466]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" type="generic">49 specimens</specimenCount>
all labelled as “cotype” (currently, 
<typeStatus box="[1279,1382,1441,1467]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">syntypes</typeStatus>
). We do not know if the type was actually selected by Petrovitz and is currently elsewhere, or if it has never been selected at all. In any case, as the species is easily identifiable using the characters indicated here below, we do not deem it necessary to designate a 
<typeStatus box="[428,534,1548,1574]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
